<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-02-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-02-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1216" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1216">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.142/1358b</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Consul at Jerusalem</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GOA1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Glazebrook</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-02-04">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 4, 1916</hi>
                                    </date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Red Cross planning send about February 15 on United States collier
                                about two tons medical supplies for Jewish hospitals Jerusalem.
                                Telegraph whether agent Jaffa can arrange send small boat meet
                                collier beyond mined area and land supplies.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>